06646nam a22008655i 9789048544974DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20222022ne     fo  d z      eng d  a97890485449747 a10.1515/97890485449742doi  a(DE-B1597)638354  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL 4aDP63b.W75 2023 7aHIS0370102bisacsh04a946.0122300aWriting History in Late Antique Iberia :bHistoriography in Theory and Practice from the 4th to the 7th Century /ced. by Purificación Ubric Rabaneda. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (312 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aLate Antique and Early Medieval Iberia ;v1000tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- t1. Writing History in Late Antique Iberia: Theory and Praxis -- t2. Para qué sirve la Historia : Principios teóricos de la historiografía hispana tardoantigua -- t3. From Christian Historiography to the Emergence of National Histories : Spanish Historiography between Romans and Visigoths -- t4. Orosius: An Iberian Patriot’s History of Rome -- t5. Orosius, Barbarians, and the Christian Success Story -- t6. Prophecies and Omens of the Fall of the Roman Empire in the Chronicle of Hydatius of Lemica -- t7. La dimensión política de los historiadores del reino visigodo de Toledo -- t8. The Definitions and Uses of Historia in Isidore of Seville -- t9. Bishops and Their Biographers : The Praxis of History Writing in Visigothic Iberia -- t10. Local Powers and Construction of the Past in the Visigothic Kingdom of Hispania -- t11. The Contemplation of the Past in the Libellus Precum of Faustinus (and Marcellinus) -- t12. Orthodoxy and Heterodoxy : The Historiography of Hispania in Late Antiquity -- t13. Expulsados de la Historia : El argumento histórico en la polémica antijudía hispana (siglos IV-VII) -- t14. Consideraciones sobre la temporalidad en las Vitae Sanctorum visigóticas -- t15. The Image of Leovigild as Arian Monarch in the ‘Vitas Patrum Emeritensium’:1 From Historical Reality to Hagiographical Deformation -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume reflects on the motivations underpinning the writing of history in Late Antique Iberia, emphasising its theoretical and practical aspects and outlining the social, political and ideological implications of the constructions and narrations of the past. The volume includes general topics related to the writing of history, such as the historiographical debates on writing history, the praxis of history writing and the role of central and local powers in the construction of the past, the legitimacy of history, the exaltation of Christian history to the detriment of other religious beliefs, and the perception of time in hagiographical texts. Further points of interest in the volume are the specific studies on the historiographical culture. All these issues are analysed from an innovative perspective, which combines traditional subjects with new historiographical topics, such as the configuration of historical discourse through another type of documentation like councils, hagiography or legislation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 4aAntiquity. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aMedieval Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aLate Antique Iberia, Early Middle Ages, Historiography, Isidore of Seville, Orosius.1 aAcerbi, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAulisa, Immacolata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBravo, Gonzalo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastellanos, Santiago, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFear, Andrew, ec